  "title": "PLATING TECHNICIAN",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Operate manufacturing equipment such as plating line and re-reeler.</li><li>Use of the measuring equipment , solder pot and X’ray machine to perform quality check on parts as per checklist.</li><li>Inspect product and material to ensure that they meet specifications.</li><li>Perform line maintenance to ensure line operation.</li><li>Maintain production data such as quantity on scrap, good part, changeover and set up hours, production hours in QAD.</li><li>Record and document appropriate information such as inspection checklist, production records etc.</li><li>Set up and changeover plating lines.</li><li>Monitor and adjust AMP reading, solution levels, line speed, line tension, jets, rinse flow, contact rollers etc.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>SPM / \"O\" Level / Professional Certificate / ITE in Mechanical or equivalent</li><li>Plating experience and chemical handling experience.</li><li>Candidates without experience will be considered for Plating Operator role (on the job training will be provided)</li><li>Able to work rotation shift</li><li>Able to commit to work Overtime</li></ul>",
